  , especially 3, with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>.","Dutch: genitivized form of   Holland  ."]},{"name":"Howland","meanings":["English: variant of   Holland  .","Americanized form of Norwegian   Hovland  .","History: Howland was the name of three Quaker brothers, original settlers in Marshfield, MA. They were from Huntingdonshire, England. The eldest, John Howland (<i>c.</i> 1593–1672) was a passenger on the <i>Mayflower</i>, servant to Gov. John Carver, who died in the first winter at Plymouth Colony."]},{"name":"Hollander","meanings":["Dutch (also <b>Den Hollander</b>), German (also <b>Holländer</b>), English, Swedish, and Jewish (Ashkenazic): habitational name for someone from Holland (see   Holland   1)."]},{"name":"Holand","meanings":["English and Scottish: variant of   Holland  .","Norwegian: habitational name from about twenty farmsteads so named, composed of Old Norse <i>hár</i> ‘high’ + <i>land</i> ‘land, field’, denoting a high-lying farm."]},{"name":"Aland","meanings":["Scandinavian (<b>Åland</b>): topographic name from the Åland Islands in the Gulf of Bothnia.","English: topographic name from Middle English <i>atte lande</i> (Old French <i>laund</i>) ‘dweller at the glade or pasture’, or sometimes perhaps, ‘dweller at the old cultivated land(s)’ from Old English <i>eald</i>, <i>ald</i> ‘old’ + <i>land</i> ‘land’."]},{"name":"Hollon","meanings":["English: altered form of   Holland  ."]}]},{"name":"son","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Ronald .  It is sometimes used as a given name in its own right."],"variants":[{"name":"Ronald","meanings":["From the Old Norse personal name <i>Rögnvaldr</i> (composed of <i>regin</i> ‘advice, decision’ (also, ‘the gods’) + <i>valdr</i> ‘ruler’). This name was regularly used in the Middle Ages in northern England and Scotland, where Scandinavian influence was strong. It is now widespread throughout the English-speaking world."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"g- son Holland was born about 1141, in Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales as the son of son Holland. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"ABT    1141–":"umbes 1141–Surnud","1141–Male":"1141–Surnud","1181–Male":"1181–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","ABT    1141":"umbes 1141","1141":"1141","1181":"1181","of Cil-sant,Llanwinio,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fi":{"ABT    1141–":"noin 1141–Kuollut","1141–Male":"1141–Kuollut","1181–Male":"1181–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","ABT    1141":"noin 1141","1141":"1141","1181":"1181","of Cil-sant,Llanwinio,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"fr":{"ABT    1141–":"environ 1141–Décédé","1141–Male":"1141–Décédé","1181–Male":"1181–Décédé","–Male":"Décédé","ABT    1141":"environ 1141","1141":"1141","1181":"1181","of Cil-sant,Llanwinio,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Galles","lifeSummary":"g- son Holland est né environ 1141, à Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Galles, fils de son Holland. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"ABT    1141–":"um 1141–Verstorben","1141–Male":"1141–Verstorben","1181–Male":"1181–Verstorben","–Male":"Verstorben","ABT    1141":"um 1141","1141":"1141","1181":"1181","of Cil-sant,Llanwinio,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales","lifeSummary":"g- son Holland wurde um 1141 in Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales, als Sohn von son Holland geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"ABT    1141–":"about 1141–Desede","1141–Male":"1141–Desede","1181–Male":"1181–Desede","–Male":"Desede","ABT    1141":"about 1141","1141":"1141","1181":"1181","of Cil-sant,Llanwinio,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"hu":{"ABT    1141–":"1141 körül–elhunyt","1141–Male":"1141–elhunyt","1181–Male":"1181–elhunyt","–Male":"elhunyt","ABT    1141":"1141 körül","1141":"1141","1181":"1181","of Cil-sant,Llanwinio,Carmarthenshire,Wales":"Llanwinio, Carmarthenshire, Wales"},"id":{"ABT    1141–":"sekitar 1141–Telah Meninggal